<![CDATA[
<img class="size-full wp-image-2764603" src="http://images.indianexpress.com/2016/04/kohli-7593.jpg" alt="Virat Kohli, Kohli, Kohli charity, Kohli pictures, Virat Kohli pictures, Virat Kohli foundation, cricketers charity, sports charity" /> <a href="http://indianexpress.com/tag/virat-kohli/">Virat Kohli</a> met people at the &#8216;Abhalmaya&#8217; old age home in Pune on Thursday. (Source: Twitter) <p>Members of the Indian cricket team and of different Indian Premier League sides, Virat Kohli, Ishant Sharma, Ajinkya Rahane and Irfan Pathan came together to do their bit towards the underprivileged part of the society. <strong>(<a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/indian-premier-league-t20-2016-schedule-full-fixtures-results-schedule-time-and-more/">Fixtures</a> | <a href="http://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket/ipl-2016-schedule-teams-tickets-squad-auction-9-streaming/">Squads</a>)</strong></p> <p>Virat Kohli visited the &#8216;Abhalmaya&#8217; old-age home in Pune in an event organised by Sundan Lele in partnership with Kohli&#8217;s charity foundation.</p> <img class="size-full wp-image-2764605" src="http://images.indianexpress.com/2016/04/kohli1-759.jpg" alt="Virat Kohli, Kohli, Kohli charity, Kohli pictures, Virat Kohli pictures, Virat Kohli foundation, cricketers charity, sports charity" /> Virat Kohli runs a charity for underprivileged kids. (Source: Twitter) <p>Kohli is part of the Royal Challengers Bangalore IPL side and has had a good tournament so far with 187 runs in three matches. Their next match is against Rising Pune Supergiants on Friday.</p> <p>Also doing their bit for charity were members of Pune Supergiants &#8211; Pathan, Rahane and Ishant as they visited children at the KEM Hospital in the city.</p> <img class="size-full wp-image-2764606" src="http://images.indianexpress.com/2016/04/ajinkya-ishant-irfan-759.jpg" alt="Ishant Sharma, Ajinkya Rahane, Irfan Pathan, Rising Pune Supergiants, Pune Supergiants, IPL 2016, IPL, cricketers charity, sports charity" /> Ishant Sharma, Irfan Pathan and Ajinkya Rahane chatted with kids at the KEM Hospital in Pune. <p>The players interacted with the children by playing games &amp; sharing their experiences on and off the field. The players saluted the unbreakable spirit of the kids and encouraged them to keep fighting!</p><img alt="" border="0" src="http://pixel.wp.com/b.gif?host=indianexpress.com&#038;blog=53855017&#038;post=2764566&#038;subd=indianexpressonline&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />
