ne&#8217;s Gabba ground tipped to be played under lights.</p> <p>Cricket Australia will announce their summer schedule on Wednesday and declined to comment on South Africa&#8217;s reservations about the pink ball.</p><img alt="" border="0" src="http://pixel.wp.com/b.gif?host=indianexpress.com&#038;blog=53855017&#038;post=2759999&#038;subd=indianexpressonline&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />
