<![CDATA[
<img class="wp-image-2758026 size-full" src="http://images.indianexpress.com/2016/04/livecricketscore53.jpg" alt="" /> Quinton de Kock scored 108 runs in Delhi&#8217;s win over Bangalore. (Source: BCCI) <p><strong>Delhi Daredevils chase down 193 against Bangalore to win by seven wickets. Quinton de Kock led the chase with a 108 supported by Karun Nair&#8217;s 54*. </strong></p> <p><strong><a href="http://indianexpress.com/cricket/scorecard/bcdd04172016181037">Cricket Scorecard: RCB vs DD (CLICK HERE)</a></strong></p> <p><strong>RCB vs DD as it happened</strong></p> <p><strong>2330 hrs IST: All over! Great chase from Delhi led by De Kock but Karun Nair with 54* also good</strong></p> <p><strong>2326 hrs IST: WICKET! De Kock gone after a super innings of 108</strong></p> <p><strong>2323 hrs IST: HUNDRED! Quinton de Kock has just made a 48-ball ton. What an innings under pressure</strong></p> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"> <p dir="ltr" lang="en">Even given the batting conditions, this is still the innings of the tournament from Quinton de Kock.</p> <p>— Harsha Bhogle (@bhogleharsha) <a href="http://twitter.com/bhogleharsha/status/721759052162727936">17 April 2016</a></p></blockquote> <p>2318 hrs IST: 13 off the 17th over and De Kock moves onto 99*</p> <p>2312 hrs IST: DD cruising now. 12 off the 16th over</p> <p>2307 hrs IST: 10 runs off the 15th over and DD need 46 off 30 balls</p> <p>2303 hrs IST: De Kock sends the last two balls of 14th over for six and four! DD need 56 off 36</p> <p>2300 hrs IST: Nair lending his support to De Kock and getting the occasional boundary</p> <p>2254 hrs IST: De Kock with a big six to start the 13th over</p> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"> <p dir="ltr" lang="en">Quinton de Kock is the match winner here, Karun Nair has to play around him. Roles clear</p> <p>— Harsha Bhogle (@bhogleharsha) <a href="http://twitter.com/bhogleharsha/status/721751036747079680">17 April 2016</a></p></blockquote> <p>2252 hrs IST: Five runs off the 12th over. DD need 87 more</p> <p>2247 hrs IST: 100 up for Delhi Daredevils at the end of the 11th over. They need 92 more runs of 54 balls</p> <p><strong>2242 hrs IST: FIFTY! Quinton de Kock gets a half-century in just 22 balls. Crucial innings in this DD chase</strong></p> <p>2237 hrs IST: 14 off the ninth over and DD are on course in the chase</p> <p>2231 hrs IST: Time for the strategic time-out</p> <p><strong>2231 hrs IST: Five runs of the eighth over and DD are 67/2. They need 125 runs off the last 12 overs</strong></p> <p>2226 hrs IST: Quinton de Kock leading the chase for DD. He is on 39 off 18 balls</p> <p>2222 hrs IST: End of powerplay and DD are 51/2</p> <p>2220 hrs IST: WICKET! Samson is gone. Too high on the bat for the pull and caught at mid-wicket</p> <p>2215 hrs IST: De Kock is not holding back. Excellent boundaries from him</p> <p>2205 hrs IST: Expensive over from Parveez Rasool. DD 24/1 after 2 overs</p> <p><strong>2200 hrs IST: WICKET! What a catch. Shane Watson runs from mid-on and grabs it before the long-on boundary but momentum carries him forward. He throws it back and Wiese dives to take it, just inches away from the ropes. Iyer gone</strong></p> <p>2155 hrs IST: Shreyas Iyer and Quinton de Kock out in the middle</p> <p><strong>2127 hrs IST: Last ball goes for four but RCB will be a little disappointed with the total &#8211; 191/5</strong></p> <p>2133 hrs IST: Shami gives only 6 runs in the 19th over</p> <p>2130 hrs IST: Shami is bowling a tremendous spell. Dot balls worth gold in death over</p> <p><strong>2128 hrs IST: WICKET! A big wicket for Delhi. Kohli is caught at long-on for 79. Shami gets his second</strong></p> <p>2127 hrs IST: What an over from Morris. Only 4 runs off it</p> <p>2123 hrs IST: <a href="http://indianexpress.com/tag/virat-kohli/">Virat Kohli</a> and Kedar Jadhav at the crease. Chris Morris to bowl the 18th over</p> <p><strong>2120 hrs IST: Run out! Sarfaraz Khan sets off for a run but Shami with an excellent pick and throw on his follow through. Superb</strong></p> <p>2117 hrs IST: Sarfaraz Khan is the new man in for Royal Challengers Bangalore</p> <p><strong>2115 hrs IST: WICKET! Shane Watson early to play the shot and it takes the top of the bat and goes to short fine-leg</strong></p> <p>2114 hrs IST: Shane Watson starts the 17th over with a straight six. A big one</p> <p>2112 hrs IST: Time for the strategic time-out</p> <p>2112 hrs IST: Virat Kohli has raced to 71 off 42 after the 16th over feteched 21 runs</p> <p><strong>2110 hrs IST: Shane Watson hits a six over fine-leg, Virat Kohli hits a six over wid-wicket. They are just sublime</strong></p> <p>2105 hrs IST: Kohli sends Mishra over cover for a six. Another four through third-man boundary</p> <p>2103 hrs IST: Shane Watson hits a six and follows it with two consecutive fours. RCB 130/2 after 14 overs</p> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"> <p dir="ltr" lang="en">They said if Lillee don&#8217;t get you Thommo will. For <a href="http://twitter.com/hashtag/RCB?src=hash">#RCB</a> read: if Gayle don&#8217;t, if AB don&#8217;t, if Virat don&#8217;t, if Watson don&#8217;t&#8230;.</p> <p>— Harsha Bhogle (@bhogleharsha) <a href="http://twitter.com/bhogleharsha/status/721723200543928320">17 April 2016</a></p></blockquote> <p>2058 hrs IST: FIFTY! Virat Kohli scores another half-century. RCB roaring</p> <p>2054 hrs IST: Excellent over from Carlos Brathwaite. Only three runs off it and the wicket of AB</p> <p>2051 hrs IST: Shane Watson is in at number four for RCB</p> <p><strong>2050 hrs IST: WICKET! </strong>AB de Villiers fails to connect one properly and is caught at long-on. Carlos Brathwaite with the breakthrough. RCB 107/2</p> <p>2048 hrs IST: Negi over fetches nine runs. Virat Kohli with a six in that over</p> <p>2044 hrs IST: FIFTY! AB de Villiers with another classy knock for RCB. Bangalore crowd applauds</p> <p>2039 hrs IST: Only one boundary in this over and RCB collect seven runs. They are 79/1 after 8 overs</p> <p>2036 hrs IST: Am